-- Lakers’ Pau Gasol to Start Against Bobcats in Return From Injury
-- B y   M i c h a e l   S i l l u p
-- 2012-12-18T19:53:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-18/lakers-pau-gasol-to-start-against-bobcats-in-return-from-injury.html
The Los Angeles Lakers’ Pau Gasol
will start tonight’s game against the Charlotte Bobcats after
being out since Dec. 3 with tendinitis in his knees, according
to the team’s website.  Coach  Mike D’Antoni  said Gasol responded well to a practice
yesterday so he will start tonight. The four-time All-Star is
averaging 12.6 points and 8.8 rebounds in 17 games. The Lakers
are 11-13 and in third place in the National Basketball
Association’s Pacific Division.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  